<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,798,969]" pageId="13" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,798,824]" pageId="13" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The only known member of the species-group is similar externally to species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1232,1381,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crinomima">
<emphasis box="[1232,1381,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="35">P. crinomima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (
<figureCitation box="[283,412,834,861]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 9–16" captionStart-1="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId-0="5.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionStartId-1="6.[151,264,1143,1167]" captionTargetBox-0="[182,1407,185,1908]" captionTargetBox-1="[168,1418,185,1110]" captionTargetId-0="figure-34@5.[167,1421,181,1920]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@6.[156,1431,181,1119]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="6" captionText-0="FIGURES 9–16. Polymixis spp.: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 9 and 10 in JSL; 11 in NSMT (photo by U. Jinbo); 12–16 in BBT." captionText-1="FIGURES 17–20. Polymixis spp.: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 17 and 18 in AFM; 19 and 20 in BBT." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5089287" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5089289" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5089287/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5089289/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="35">Figs 15–20</figureCitation>
), but its male genitalia are clearly different from those of other groups of the subgenus by the massive vinculum, the valva being very broad basally and having a wide clavus and an elongate and narrow dorsal costal protrusion, and the almost symmetrical digiti which are strongly asymmetrical in other groups. In the female genitalia, the elongate ovipositor and short signa bursae are characteristic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
